# proxy-api

HAProxy Dynamic Config REST API — Installation & Operations Guide

---

## Overview

`proxy-api` is a lightweight Flask-based REST API that manages HAProxy TCP tunnel configurations dynamically. It creates, deletes, and reloads per-port `listen` blocks in HAProxy without downtime, using the HAProxy master socket for zero-disruption reloads.

Each tenant gets a dedicated port mapped to a backend node IP. Configs are written as `listen` blocks in isolated `.cfg` files under `/run/haproxy/tenants/`.

**Architecture:**
- Flask API runs as a systemd service under the dedicated `proxy-api` user
- HAProxy reads tenant configs from `/run/haproxy/tenants/*.cfg` via `conf-dir`
- Reloads triggered via HAProxy master socket using `socat` — zero dropped connections
- Rollback on failed reload — config is restored automatically

---

## Prerequisites

| Requirement  | Details                                      |
|--------------|----------------------------------------------|
| OS           | Ubuntu 20.04 / 22.04 / Debian 11+            |
| HAProxy      | 2.4+ with master-worker mode enabled         |
| Python       | 3.8 or newer                                 |
| Packages     | socat, python3-venv, python3-pip             |
| Permissions  | sudo / root access required for setup        |

> **Warning:** HAProxy must be running in master-worker mode with the master socket exposed at `/run/haproxy-master.sock` before starting `proxy-api`.

---

## HAProxy Configuration

Before installing proxy-api, configure HAProxy to support dynamic tenant config loading and expose its master socket.

### Step 1 — Enable master-worker mode

Edit `/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg` and add/confirm the global section:

```
global
    master-worker
    stats socket /run/haproxy-master.sock mode 660 level admin expose-fd listeners
    stats timeout 30s

    # Load tenant configs dynamically
    conf-dir /run/haproxy/tenants
```

> The `conf-dir` directive tells HAProxy to include all `.cfg` files in that directory. `proxy-api` writes one file per tenant port into this directory.

### Step 2 — Set socket permissions

```bash
# Ensure haproxy group exists
groupadd -f haproxy

# Set socket ownership so proxy-api can send reload commands
chown root:haproxy /run/haproxy-master.sock
chmod 660 /run/haproxy-master.sock
```

### Step 3 — Restart HAProxy

```bash
systemctl restart haproxy
systemctl status haproxy

# Verify master socket exists
ls -la /run/haproxy-master.sock
```

---

## Installation

### Step 1 — Install system dependencies

```bash
apt-get update
apt-get install -y socat python3 python3-venv python3-pip
```

### Step 2 — Create system user and directories

```bash
# Dedicated unprivileged service user
useradd -r -s /bin/false proxy-api

mkdir -p /opt/proxy-api
mkdir -p /etc/proxy-api
mkdir -p /var/log/proxy-api

chown -R proxy-api:proxy-api /opt/proxy-api /var/log/proxy-api
```

### Step 3 — Deploy application

```bash
cp proxysql_api.py /opt/proxy-api/app.py

chown proxy-api:proxy-api /opt/proxy-api/app.py
chmod 644 /opt/proxy-api/app.py
```

### Step 4 — Set up Python virtual environment

```bash
cd /opt/proxy-api
sudo -u proxy-api python3 -m venv venv
sudo -u proxy-api venv/bin/pip install --upgrade pip
sudo -u proxy-api venv/bin/pip install flask pymysql psycopg2-binary
```

### Step 5 — Create tenant config directory

```bash
mkdir -p /run/haproxy/tenants

# Add proxy-api to haproxy group so it can write configs and use the socket
usermod -aG haproxy proxy-api

chown proxy-api:haproxy /run/haproxy/tenants
chmod 775 /run/haproxy/tenants

# Persist directory across reboots (tmpfs is cleared on boot)
tee /etc/tmpfiles.d/haproxy-tenants.conf > /dev/null <<EOF
d /run/haproxy/tenants 0775 proxy-api haproxy -
EOF
```

### Step 6 — Create environment file

```bash
tee /etc/proxy-api/env > /dev/null <<EOF
API_PORT=8080
API_HOST=0.0.0.0
PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1
EOF

chmod 600 /etc/proxy-api/env
chown proxy-api:proxy-api /etc/proxy-api/env
```

### Step 7 — Install systemd service

```bash
tee /etc/systemd/system/proxy-api.service > /dev/null <<EOF
[Unit]
Description=HAProxy Dynamic Config REST API (proxy-api)
After=network.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=proxy-api
Group=proxy-api
WorkingDirectory=/opt/proxy-api
EnvironmentFile=/etc/proxy-api/env
ExecStart=/opt/proxy-api/venv/bin/python /opt/proxy-api/app.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

# Security hardening
NoNewPrivileges=true
PrivateTmp=true
ProtectSystem=full
ProtectHome=true
ReadWritePaths=/var/log/proxy-api

# Logging
StandardOutput=journal
StandardError=journal
SyslogIdentifier=proxy-api

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF
```

### Step 8 — Enable and start the service

```bash
systemctl daemon-reload
systemctl enable proxy-api
systemctl start proxy-api
systemctl status proxy-api
```

### Step 9 — Verify installation

```bash
curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/health

# Expected response:
# {"message": "HAProxy config API is healthy", "status": "ok"}
```

---

## API Reference

Base URL: `http://<server-ip>:8080`

| Method   | Endpoint            | Description                       | Required Fields          |
|----------|---------------------|-----------------------------------|--------------------------|
| GET      | /health             | Health check                      | —                        |
| GET      | /haproxy/configs    | List all active tenant configs    | —                        |
| POST     | /haproxy/config     | Create config & reload HAProxy    | port, node_ip, db_port   |
| DELETE   | /haproxy/config     | Delete config & reload HAProxy    | port                     |
| POST     | /haproxy/reload     | Manually trigger HAProxy reload   | —                        |

---

### POST /haproxy/config — Create Tunnel

Creates a new HAProxy `listen` block that forwards the given port to the target node.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "port":    3307,
  "node_ip": "10.0.0.5",
  "db_port": 3306
}
```

> **All three fields are required. There is no default for `db_port` — omitting any field returns a 400 error.**

**Generated HAProxy config:**
```
listen node_3307
    bind *:3307
    mode tcp
    option tcplog
    server db1 10.0.0.5:3306 check
```

**Success response (200):**
```json
{
  "status": "ok",
  "message": "HAProxy config for port 3307 created and reloaded (-> 10.0.0.5:3306)"
}
```

---

### DELETE /haproxy/config — Remove Tunnel

Removes the config for the specified port and reloads HAProxy. Rolls back automatically if reload fails.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "port": 3307
}
```

---

### GET /haproxy/configs — List Active Tunnels

```json
{
  "status": "ok",
  "message": "success",
  "data": ["3307.cfg", "3308.cfg", "5433.cfg"]
}
```

---

## Operations

**View live logs:**
```bash
journalctl -u proxy-api -f
journalctl -u proxy-api -n 100
```

**Restart service:**
```bash
systemctl restart proxy-api
```

**Check active tenant configs:**
```bash
ls -la /run/haproxy/tenants/
cat /run/haproxy/tenants/3307.cfg
```

**Manual HAProxy reload:**
```bash
# Via API
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/haproxy/reload

# Directly via socket
echo 'reload' | socat stdio /run/haproxy-master.sock
```

**Rollback behaviour:**
If an HAProxy reload fails after a config change, `proxy-api` automatically restores the previous config before returning a 500 error. No manual intervention is needed.

---

## Troubleshooting

| Problem                              | Fix                                                                                              |
|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Reload failed: permission denied     | Run `usermod -aG haproxy proxy-api` then restart the service                                    |
| Socket not found                     | HAProxy is not in master-worker mode or socket path is wrong. Check `/run/haproxy-master.sock`  |
| Tenant dir missing after reboot      | Ensure `/etc/tmpfiles.d/haproxy-tenants.conf` exists, then run `systemd-tmpfiles --create`      |
| db_port missing field error          | `db_port` is required with no default — always pass all three fields: `port`, `node_ip`, `db_port` |
| Port already in use                  | A config for that port already exists. DELETE it first, or POST again to overwrite              |

---

## File Reference

| Path                                        | Description                                  |
|---------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| `/opt/proxy-api/app.py`                     | Main Flask application                       |
| `/etc/proxy-api/env`                        | Environment variables (API_PORT, API_HOST)   |
| `/etc/systemd/system/proxy-api.service`     | Systemd service unit                         |
| `/run/haproxy/tenants/<port>.cfg`           | Per-tenant HAProxy listen block              |
| `/etc/tmpfiles.d/haproxy-tenants.conf`      | Ensures tenant dir is recreated on boot      |
| `/var/log/proxy-api/`                       | Log directory (journald is primary)          |